# Project context and skills

This repository is the **Default Context Generator**. Use the context documentation and the skills below to keep things consistent.

## Where the context is

- **Overview and index:** [docs/context/README.md](../../docs/context/README.md)
- **By area:** [extension.md](../../docs/context/extension.md), [skills-e-rules.md](../../docs/context/skills-e-rules.md), [technical-docs.md](../../docs/context/technical-docs.md), [doc-existing-repos.md](../../docs/context/doc-existing-repos.md), [i18n.md](../../docs/context/i18n.md)

## Skill allocation (in this repo)

| When working on | Use as guide |
|-----------------|--------------|
| `src/extension.ts`, commands, clipboard, VS Code API | [VS Code Extension API](https://code.visualstudio.com/api), [TypeScript](https://www.typescriptlang.org/docs/), [docs/context/extension.md](../../docs/context/extension.md). |
| `src/nls.ts`, `package.nls*.json`, UI copy / webview text | Rule **i18n**; for popup labels and flows also **ux-ui**; for keyboard/ARIA in webviews **accessibility**. |
| `.cursor/skills/`, `.cursor/rules/`, generator Markdown content | **technical-docs** (structure, Cursor format); **default-context-generator** for the full workflow. |
| `README.md`, `docs/`, `docs/context/` | **technical-docs**; keep in sync with code and `.cursor/`. |
| Request to "generate context" or "get context" | Rule **gerar-contexto** + skill **default-context-generator** (see `.cursor/rules/gerar-contexto.mdc`). |

## Keep documentation up to date

When you change code, architecture, or conventions that affect what is described in `docs/context/` (or in README.md), **update the corresponding document in the same workflow**. That avoids drift between code and context and keeps the context in sync with the current state.

